label.value: resistance to methionine

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of methionine than normal.

definition.value: To be annotated in situations where the aminoacid is used as a drug (high concentrations), not as a carbon/sulfur/nitrogen source.

label.value: resistance to hydroxyurea and methyl methanesulfonate

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of higher concentrations of hydroxyurea and methyl methanesulfonate than normal.

label.value: increased cell population growth on ammonium nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population phenotype in which cell growth is increased relative to normal in a medium containing ammonium as the nitrogen source.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: increased cell population growth on glutamate nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population phenotype in which cell growth is increased relative to normal in a medium containing glutamate as the nitrogen source.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: decreased cell population growth on glutamate nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing L-glutamate as the nitrogen source.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: increased viabilitiy in stationary phase upon glucose starvation

definition.value: A cell population phenotype in which a higher than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable after entering stationary phase, when subjected to glucose starvation.

label.value: resistance to ethyl methanesulfonate

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of ethyl methanesulfonate than normal.

label.value: decreased kinetochore microtubule depolymerization during mitotic anaphase A

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which kinetochore microtubule depolymerization, i.e. the removal of tubulin dimers from a kinetochore microtubule, occurs to a lesser extent than normal during anaphase A. Kinetochore microtubule depolymerisation drives chromosome movement during Anaphase A in S. pombe.

label.value: decreased rate of microtubule catastrophe involved in meitotic centromere clustering during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cellular process in which catastrophe rate (i.e. the frequency of transition from pause or growth to shrinkage) of microtubules is lower than normal as part of centromere clustering during meiotic prophase I.

label.value: decreased microtubule depolymerisation involved in meitotic centromere clustering during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cellular process in which depolymerization (i.e. removal of tubulin dimers) of microtubules as part of centromere clustering during meiotic prophase I is decreased with respect to normal. This can happen due to lower catastrophe rate or depolymerisation speed.

label.value: increased protein localization to cell cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: resistance to wortmannin

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of wortmannin than normal.

label.value: increased protein localization to cell cortex during mitotic interphase

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in mitotic interphase in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex is increased.
We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
higher protein localization to cell cortex during mitotic interphase

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show decreased sensitivity to X-rays.

label.value: sensitive to X-rays during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to X-rays.

label.value: sensitive to X-rays and rapamycin during vegetative growth.

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to a combination of X-rays and ramapycin.

label.value: resistance to X-rays and rapamycin during vegetative growth

definition.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased resistance to a combination of X-rays and ramapycin.
